My wife and I love to travel and eat out - whenever possible, we sit outside, not only because typically it's nicer, but also the opportunities for people watching are better. Listening to the conversations all around us is fascinating, too. And yes, occassionally we will chat people up. It happens most often in Germany, where it's more common than anywhere else in Europe for additonal people to sit at your table.

One of our favorite pastimes is guessing the language people are speaking. Most are very easy to recognize, but it can get quite challenging. It once took us something like 20 minutes to realize the couple at the next table were speaking one of the German dialects of the US (Pennsylvania German?). Another time we came to the conclusion what we were hearing must have been Papiamentu, the creole of Curacao. We were in the middle of the German Harz, where almost all tourists are Germans, which made the realization quite fascinating.

